<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Fleet xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <Name>Blue Wing</Name>
  <Version>3</Version>
  <TotalPoints>3000</TotalPoints>
  <FactionKey>KUIPER/kuiper</FactionKey>
  <Description>Difficulty: &lt;color=yellow&gt;MODERATE&lt;/color&gt;
Blue Wing "Skirmishers" is a task force centered around Aggression, Mid-Range Firepower, Electronic Warfare, and Contesting Objectives Through Map Presence.
Composed of a main formation of two Vespera cruisers and a jamming and targeting corvette along with three Kyve gunships intended to operate on their own to take objectives.
The goal of this fleet is to take control of key objectives while chipping away at enemy forces both heavy and light. Supporting a trio of cannon equipped Kyves, The Magnum equipped Vespera light cruiser has a uniquely class-leading capability to punch into heavier assets. Utilized in conjuction superior mobility and electronic warfare allows the Vesperas to operate agressively with relative impunity but beware of being engaged in cross-fire or being flanked. Jamming has difficulty working in multiple directions. The Vespera is NOT a survivable asset so treat it with care.
This fleet has the benefit of providing considerable air defense to ships around it.
Notes:
-Though the Vesperas are equipped with their own independent radars capable of fireable tracks, this is merely a backup or used to operate independently. It is highly suggested while in formation to operate the Vesperas Radar Off and Comms Recieve Only to maximize their ability to hide under jamming. Relying on the escorting Kyve to provide fire control locks.
-For Jam Resistence, the Vesperas are equipped with burnthrough pulse generators. Used in rapid succession this can give a track through jamming.
-The castles present on the Kyves and Vesperas are dual-in-role. Providing long range defense against craft and missiles along with softening lighter assets.
-Though the damage of castles is good into light assets they are incapable of breaking reinforced modules. Utilize the 50mm Magnums to secure kills.
 </Description>
  <SortOverrideOrder>5</SortOverrideOrder>
